##"Asia's largest community" in Tiantongyuan

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

The following article is from the Chinese Philanthropist magazine, by Fan Yinghua and Wu Keyan

China News Service, director, China Newsweek. Based in China, we focus on global charity and social issues, providing professional and rational reports and analyses with depth and temperature.

Nearly 500,000 people fought against the epidemic in their communities,

The density of floating population and the difficulty of social governance sinking

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tiantongyuan is crowded with outsiders. Since February 6, the Beijing Center for Disease Control and Prevention has released a series of new cases of activity in residential areas or sites, the community of Tiantongyuan accounted for 6 cases.

From the earliest spread of restrictions on the return of non-local people to the community, to Tiantong East Garden Area 2 was included in the list of newly confirmed cases three times, Tiantong Garden has become a hot topic. With a large resident population and a large number of tenants returning to Beijing, the pressure to prevent and control the outbreak in Tiantongyuan, known as the "largest community in Asia" , is enormous.

As a "big Mac" community, it is a microcosm of the mega-city, but also in the fight against the epidemic highlights a lot of grass-roots governance problems.

We're severely understaffed

Chinese philanthropist found in an interview that as the number of people returning to Beijing from other parts of the country continues to grow, the Tiantongyuan community is also on the alert. There are prominent red signs at the gates of the community that read: residents returning to Beijing from other parts of the country must register with the community, no one gets in or out of the compound until his temperature is normal.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Registered visitors to Beijing will be issued with blue temporary passes and pink temporary passes after 14 days of isolation.

There are few pedestrians on the main streets, except for security guards, residents' committees and community workers who wear the red armbands of "Changping District Volunteers" . Occasionally from the supermarket procurement of goods home residents passing, also wearing a mask, in a hurry.

Although part of the city's suburbs, Changping District Tiantongyuan is one of the most densely populated areas outside Beijing because of its proximity to the subway and the availability of rental housing. According to statistics, among Changping District's 1.889 million permanent residents, about 863,000 live in Huilongguan and Tiantongyuan. Tiantongyuan has 16 districts, 645 buildings and nearly half a million residents.

Tiantongyuan is known as the "sleeping city" , the job (industry) residence (place) separation is serious. According to the Changping District Bureau of Manpower and Social Security and big data analysis of Josiah Goddard maps, the vast majority of people who return to work have an employment radius of more than 10 km and work in the main urban areas.

With the increasing number of people returning to Beijing, the pressure of community prevention and control work is also transmitted to the streets, community managers and volunteers.

Chinese philanthropist learned from the Changping District government that starting from the afternoon of the first day of the New Year, party members, cadres, social workers and volunteers in the South Street community of Tiantongyuan have been going through their files one by one, contacting the residents of the district by telephone, with the emphasis on asking whether they are going out of Beijing, and stressed that Beijing personnel must contact the Beijing Residents Committee for registration, self-conscious isolation observation at home for 14 days.

Before New Year's Eve, Yoo Gun, who had returned to Beijing from a county in Hubei Province, rented a room in a residential area called Nanyuan in Tiantong. He told China philanthropist that he had received dozens of phone calls in the days since his return. From the police station to the neighborhood committee, all departments are asking him from where back to Beijing, where to go, the current state of health and so on. To avoid trouble, he didn't get out much during the holiday, relying entirely on online shopping to stock up on food and supplies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A delivery guy with two cell phones kept talking. Cell closed management, express delivery personnel shall not enter, the recipient can only go out to pick up the cell. The delivery guy says he's never been less productive.

Behind the intensive phone calls is huge pressure for prevention and control, and the huge population base is overwhelming the staff.

Take the North Street of Tiantongyuan as an example. There are 9 communities under the jurisdiction of this street. There are 6 super-large communities with 5,000 resident households. There are 5,806 households and 15,389 residents in the first community of Tiantongyuan alone. But the Party branch, the Neighborhood Committee staff only 9 people, that is, an average staff service 645 households, 2,564 residents, a clear shortage of staff.

Less people and more work also make the oversight of daily prevention and control inevitable.

According to the festival returned to Beijing Residents Xiao Li observation, her unit at the door of the staff did not go through the door of the residents to check the pass, there is no temperature. Xiao Li recalled, just back to Beijing a few days can still smell the smell of alcohol disinfection corridor, the elevator also has a disposable post-it notes for residents in the elevator when do protection. But in recent days, Xiao Li found that one-time post-it notes often "out of stock. ".

To make up for the shortage of manpower, the Changping District Epidemic Prevention and Control Work Leading Group requested that all district departments sink to the grass-roots level to support community prevention and control. Among them, in the South Street of Tiantongyuan, Changping District Science and Technology Commission arranged a total of 40 Party members, cadres and workers to Tiantongyuan second community to assist in the prevention and control of the epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tiantongyuan many residential areas at the door are "heavily guarded. ". It has become the norm to carry out strict registration management of people and vehicles entering and leaving the residential area.

In Tiantongyuan, the volunteers wearing the red armbands of "Changping District volunteers" are mostly older residents and security guards in various communities, with few young people, the Chinese philanthropist found in a field visit. A street patrol staff member of a neighborhood committee told the reporter that these retired elderly people usually do voluntary service for the community is OK, but in fact during the epidemic more easily become infected.

In response to the problem of insufficient number of volunteers and older age, some community organizations in Tiantongyuan have also started to recruit volunteers among the young residents through the network.

Limited participation of owners

The Yangchuan family, who live in the North Garden of Tiantong, has been holed up at home since the Spring Festival. They dare not go anywhere. His community was divided into four sections, with most entrances and exits blocked and no movement between communities.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In order to reduce the risk of infection, residents are trying to stay at home.

Yangchuan felt that the biggest change is that after the outbreak of the outbreak of the neighborhood committees, street communities to mobilize residents to establish owners wechat group, the group issued streets, Neighborhood Committees of all kinds of information, owners inform each other. He felt that this Tiantongyuan each residential area, building owners group really helped a lot, "why in the past did not establish such a community interaction channel earlier? "

Xiao Qiu, who lives in Tiantong Zhongyuan, said her neighborhood committee conducted a house-to-house survey after the outbreak, and also established a group of owners, and informed them of the relevant matters and progress. The community organized delivery channels, what needs to group in the reservation, the next day by regional distribution.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In order to avoid personal contact, the shopping platform of the new contactless distribution storage point.

According to Xiao Qiu, through wechat groups, owners will also pay attention to each other's neighbors, focusing on the check-out when the marked rental housing, such as to see the return to Beijing in the group report, by the community to negotiate.

As to whether the owners'committee plays a role in this, many residents interviewed, including Yang Chuan and Xiao Qiu, said that they did not see what the owners'committee did, and they did not even know whether there was a owners'committee.

Mao Shoulong, a professor at the School of Public Management at Renmin University of China, told China philanthropist that with the current grass roots organization structure of the community, it is difficult to do all the work. The Community Staff is few, the strength that relies on neighborhood committee alone is not enough.

Mao Shoulong believes that for such a multi-tenant, densely populated community, the owner should still be the first responsible person of the community, the owner should invite the tenants as representatives to participate in the organization and management of the community. From the current government epidemic prevention work documents, there is no launch of the main force in a very important position, only focus on the work of the Neighborhood Committee. In fact, the government should encourage more owners to participate in community management in order to do a good job in epidemic prevention.

Flexible Prevention and control scale

After the Wuhan outbreak, as Beijing stepped up prevention and control measures, there was also news on the Internet that people and vehicles from other parts of Tiantongyuan were not allowed to enter the community after January 30. Although north and south streets in Tiantongyuan have refuted the rumors, it also reflects people's sensitivity to the pressure of control brought about by the return of the tide.

On the one hand, the huge community with large floating population and dense returning population must guard against and strictly control the cross infection of potential virus carriers, and on the other hand, ensure the normal flow and life of returning population. It's a dilemma for managers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tian Tong East Garden Area 2 came the motor roar, through the block block can be seen that the staff are spray disinfection. February 17, new cases of active community, including this community.

The community is one of the most important aspects of prevention and control, said the associate researcher of the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences. The community should master the route of residents returning to Beijing and the daily journey after returning to Beijing, it is also necessary to reach out to Beijing residents. This information is also useful for tracking close contacts in the event of a confirmed case.

According to the government of Beijing, anyone returning to Beijing from Feb. 14 should stay at home or be under observation for 14 days. In the Tiantongyuan region, returnees have been ordered to head to the district-level hub at the Kyoto Conference Center on the Yellow River in Tiantongyuan for observation and isolation, at their own expense (including 280 yuan per person per day for meals) .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The community workers are explaining the points to note for vaccination to foreigners.

Tang Jun, director of the Crisis Management Research Center at Renmin University of China, told the Chinese philanthropist that such densely populated communities in Tiantongyuan are similar to Amoy Gardens in Hong Kong during SARS in 2003 because of the high risk of the environment, naturally, the level of epidemic prevention and control should be higher, and the territorial government should consider allocating a higher proportion of resources to strengthen prevention and control measures.

Tang also said that with the passage of time, after the risk level of the epidemic has been reduced, it is necessary to strike a balance between risk management and normalization and humanization of social governance in order to ensure the normal operation of social order.
